<br>
WRONG - the point system was an afterthought put into place after (weeks after) the server opened.  Using the tired old &quot;you knew the rules&quot; argument is sad to begin with, but it doesn't even apply here.  If you need points to tell you who is winning or who is good at pvp, you're pretty simple minded I'd have to say.  Again I say, if this server is about the teams, the point system has nothing to do with the teams and should go.  If it's about the points, then officially change the name and scope of the server from the deity war server to the high point server. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=FAEBD7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/unonecn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>none CN</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>poon</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/16/01 4:39:42 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> .</span><hr size=1> Three thoughts.<br>
<br>
-return the resist table to what it was-<br>
<br>
Those of a higher level should enjoy some advantage in PvP.  Speak all you want about blue server players who level all day, but the reality is someone will always have more time to play than you do.  If someone can rush to 60, good for him.  <br>
<br>
Something else to consider.  Should the resist changes stay in place, think about how it will affect the endgame.  How fun will it be for casters when the level 30 warriors that resisted every root turn level 60?  How balanced will it be when everyone plays a melee class out of frustration?  <br>
<br>
I face as many red cons as I do green cons.  There are tactics that let either side survive or prevail.  The EQ PvP system is not without flaws, but this short-sighted change, though it might seem fun now, will wreck casters and balance long term.<br>
<br>
-allow players to dispell the enemy-<br>
<br>
Want green cons to have a chance against red cons without harming late game balance?  Then allow people to dispell the enemy.  Pumice and cancel magic are not the end all to beating a red con, but the opportunity to dispell a 200 HP buff or SoW might give a crew of greens the chance they need to topple the red druid chasing them.<br>
<br>
-make zero points the fewest for any PvP kill (non-repetitive)-<br>
<br>
This is a PvP server.  Perhaps the 'most' PvP of them all.  Why punish someone for engaging in PvP?  This server is set up as a war of faith.  If the most 'fervent' are actively fighting, it makes no sense to dissuade them and force them back to item_camp8456.  All the negative points do is add one more reason not to PvP.  There are too many reason not to fight already.  Don't add more Verant, don't add more.<br>
<br>
Clarification.  The negative points for repeat kills in an hour should remain.  Not so much for bind point deaths (learn to /q), more so for the exploits possible should someone have two accounts or a friend on the other team.<br>
