</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=FAEBD7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/bsullonzektavern.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=vairus>Vairus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>poon</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/16/01 5:15:38 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re: </span><hr size=1> &quot;What? I remember on the very first post I saw regarding Sullon they were talking about putting up a scoreboard. What the hell are you talking about? Afterthought my arse.&quot;<br>
<br>
Talked about != implemented.  Points were not in place when the server opened.  The point system was not defined when the server opened.  That makes the point system an afterthought, and also makes it not part of the rules when the server opened.  Therefore to use the argument that you knew the rules when you joined/when the server opened is plainly invalid.  That's what I'm talking about.<br>
<br>
As I said before, I don't need to the point system to know who's winning.  I know neutral is winning, it's obvious without the points.  I don't understand what you are saying about using the point system to make excuses - I'm hoping that is directed toward the evil team.  I haven't heard anyone on the good team use points as an excuse. I'm on the good team, we're getting our asses kicked most of the time, I acknowledge that - don't need the point system to realize that either.  We'll keep fighting though.<br>
<br>
My real question is:  Most people have agreed that the point system doesn't really reflect which team is winning.  So what exactly does it do then?  Show us who's best at manipulating an obviously poorly implemented scoring system?  When last I checked this was a PvP server, you don't need a point system to encourage PvP, it's going to happen.  And maybe it's discouraged reds from farming greens directly, but it took manipulators of the point system about 30 seconds to find a way around that via the set up kills for my low level buddy system.  So it hasn't really stopped green farming either.  All the point system has done is take the focus away from the diety war and put it on how many easy point kills can I get today.  That being the case, out it should go, unless Verant explicitly states that the actual focus of the server is collecting points.<br>
<br>
I'll make it simple for you:<br>
If the point system makes it such that there is even one case where someone who would normally blast every green in an enemy's home land does not do so because they are afraid of losing points, then the point system has failed to work in the context of the server, and should be removed.<br>
if the point system makes it such that there is even one case where someone who should be defending their homeland against an incursion of even level oppressors decides to go farm lowbies for points instead because it would be easier to get points that way, then the point system has failed to work in the context of the server, and should be removed.<br>
These are just two situations in which the point system detrimentally affects the advertised dynamic of the server (deity war).  These situations occur multiple times on a daily basis.  Removing the point system would remove these situations.  Removing these situations would help enforce the advertised server dynamic.  Therefore the point system should be removed. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#DEB887><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/uveloxargentum.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Velox Argentum</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>poon</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/16/01 5:15:54 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re:</span><hr size=1> They should NOT return the resist table to what it was, they should make the &quot;slight&quot; adjustments the patchmessage claimed. Resists as they were wasn't a viable solution for an open PvP level range, however with this new change they went way too far. They should have about halved the impact levels had on resists and not messed with it any more, that would let people 10 levels below somebody to have a half decent chance atleast. <p><b>Velox Argentum</b><BR>
