Your initial statement was that we knew the rules when we started on the server and shouldn't have expected otherwise.  I argued on that basis - the points were not in effect when I signed up, therefore your initial argument was invalid.  Now you have flip flopped and said the rules have changed and we should deal with it.  You've just contradicted your initial postition.  Regardless of your poor debating skills - I do deal with it, I ignore the points.  I don't care about the points, I believe the points have no bearing on who is actually &quot;winning&quot;.  The point system does seem to have had a detrimental effect on some (SOME not ALL) people on the server in relation to their functioning within the advertised dynamic of the server (deity war).  That is what I'm commenting on.  Since the points don't reflect who is winning, and they are detrimental (I believe this to be so, others don't) it is logical to remove the point system.<br>
